    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle Street</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden New Jersey</name>
                    <date when="1884-08-04" rend="right">August 4 1884</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir<ptr target="duk.00798_n1"/></salute>
            </opener>
            <p>In answer to your letter &#38; request a few days ago <hi rend= "italic">Yes</hi> I will gladly write for the
                <hi rend= "italic">Century</hi> an article on the Hospitals &#38; Hospital Nursing of the Secession War,
                such as outlined by you&#8212;I will set about it immediately&#8212;</p>
            <p>I enclose a short sketch &#38; reminiscence of Father Taylor, with authentic
                portrait, (given me by his daughter). The price is $50&#8212;If you use it I would
                want to see proof, &#38; would like to reserve the right of printing it in future
                book&#8212;Say after the lapse of a year&#8212;Respects to Watson
                Gilder<ptr target="duk.00798_n2"/>&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            
        </body>
    </text>
